   <mods:abstract>Resolved, that Congress approves entirely of JayÆs actions, including the
            restriction he put on the limitation he proposed concerning the navigation of the
            Mississippi. Believes proposal just, that giving up the navigation of the Mississippi
            removed the only purported obstacle to an alliance between the two countries. Was seen
            as the price paid for the benefits of an early and intimate connection; which sacrifice
            would no longer have an value at the end of the war; that each day of delay in
            concluding the treaty diminished the obligation and desire of the United States to hold
            to their initial initiative. Wants Jay to let the Spanish understand that Congress
            expects a liberal treaty after all the delays -- either an augmentation of monetary aid
            and a stipulation facilitating United States navigation of the Mississippi, or a
            particular concession concerning commerce of the Spanish colonies in the America. In
            French.</mods:abstract>
